==English==
===Etymology===
Latin comparative of ''[[posterus]]'' coming after

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪəriə(r)|-ɪəriə(r)]]

===Adjective===
'''posterior'''

# [[locate]]d [[behind]], or [[towards]] the [[rear]] of an [[object]]
# in [[anatomy]], the [[caudal]] end of the [[body]] in [[quadruped]]s, and the [[dorsal]] end in [[biped]]s
# in [[botany]], next to, or facing the main [[stem]] or [[axis]]
# [[following]] in [[order]] or in [[time]]

====Antonyms====
*[[anterior]]

===Noun===
'''posterior'''

# the [[buttocks]]

